groupadd, easy command to add a new group
executable location: '/bin/groupadd.sh'  alias: 'groupadd'
groupadd is part of the 'auth-client' app

used to quickly create a new group on AUTH

syntax: 'groupadd groupname'

any logged in user can create a group
the user will get marked as "owner" for AUTH purpuses.
this is seperate from the actual ownership of the system (AUTH)
only admins and makers can delete a group.
users need to be logged in and networked to adjust a group.